documents.title: the day after the election the day before
text: here we are at day - 1 of the queensland election .
on a sunday afternoon we are still in the same position we were late on saturday night - no result .
here is what we know , right now , in this minute : with 71.4 % of the vote counter labor have 43 seats and the liberal national party has 39 seats with a swing away from the government of 11.4 % .
45 seats are needed for a party to form government in its own right .
four seats are currently on knife edge and the outcome will likely not be known for days .

katter 's australian party has two seats and independent peter wellington has retained his seat , the trio could form a balance of power despite campbell newman and annastacia palaszczuk ruling out doing deals with minor parties before the election .
tony abbott says there are lessons to be learnt from the queensland election result but he backed away from saying there were federal factors at play in the election .
campbell newman spent the morning packing up his office but when asked about the result he responded i 'm just one guy with one vote now .
a confident annstacia palaszczuk declared she would govern for all queenslanders at a supporters ' barbecue where she did not take any questions from the media .
the lnp will meet in coming days to determine who the new leader of the party will be now campbell newman has lost his seat of ashgrove .
and with that the queensland election live blog comes to a halt .
until next time queenslanders and queenslanders ' distant admirers .

antony green hath spoken antony green ( @ antonygreenabc ) if everyone had followed lnp advice and just voted 1 , the lnp would have 51 seats # qldvotes for those playing at home , that 's six more than the amount the lnp needed to retain majority government .
no wonder the lnp tried to send such a clear message yesterday
the liberal national party room will meet this week and vote in a new leader .
so who will they be voting for ?

there are three main contenders : education minister , john-paul langbroek health minister lawrence springborg treasurer tim nicholls deputy premier , jeff seeney , is also a possibility but it is not expected he will put his hand up for the gig .
seeney and nicholls could potentially be seen as too close to campbell newman and may cop some of the anger from returning mps after losing government .
transport minister , scott emerson , is a dark horse for the job but this is a leadership contest , there are no contenders until there are contenders .
the lnp may be looking to bring in some fresh blood and revamp itself - springborg and langbroek have both been opposition leaders before .
here are some snap profiles my colleague joshua robertson and i put together on the obvious contenders earlier in the campaign .
fred mcconnell ( @ fred dash ) one cartoonist quick off the mark reflecting on lnp 's leadership dilemmas today # qldvotes brought to you from the pen of matt golding .

documents.title: kevin andrews : very little involvement from federal liberals in the election
text: defence minister , kevin andrews , is singing from the same song sheet as his boss , tony abbott , - we have lessons to learn from queensland but federal factors were not a major factor .
we are proud , obviously , of the work campbell newman and his government have done .
we have to learn lessons from any election that occurs , particularly one where you do n't do so well .
while reform is needed we need to explain to the australian people why reform is needed .
but , he says , the queensland election was fought entirely on state issues and there was very little involvement from their federal counterparts .

documents.title: annastacia palaszczuk : we will govern for all of you
text: queensland labor leader , annastacia palaszczuk , has declared she will govern for all of queensland .
sounding very confident of becoming premier , palaszczuk said the result will not be known for a few days but queenslanders had sent a message .

it is extremely humbling and we are going to restore good government to this state , good , stable government and a govt that works for all of queensland , it does n't matter where you live across this state , we will govern for all of you .
palaszczuk was also possibly making a pitch to katter 's australian party , which has won two seats so could hold the balance of power , and is staunchly anti-privatisation .
queenslanders sent a message loud and clear right across the state , they do not want their assets sold .
and what is clear is it does n't matter who leads the lnp , whether it 's tim nicholls , scott emerson , lawrence springborg , john-paul langbroek or jeff seeney , they want to sell your assets .
that is their only plan and labor will stop that sale .
that is one happy lady :
labor supporters are being kept in the loop on annastacia palaszczuk and bill shorten 's totally casual pen-palling .
vote labor ( @ vote labor ) annastacia palaszczuk and bill shorten say thank you .
# thisislabor # qldvotes here 's a larger version to zoom in on .

tony abbott has vowed to learn the lessons of the liberal national party 's electoral trouncing in queensland , as shell-shocked mps weigh other leadership options amid doubts the prime minister can turn around the federal government 's fortunes , daniel hurst reports here .

abbott 's position is under intense pressure as he prepares to address the national press club on monday to outline the government 's agenda for the year a speech that liberal mp jane prentice said would be a make-or-break moment .

the queensland results are another blow to abbott after the government 's ragged end to the 2014 parliamentary year marked by mixed messages and u-turns on key policies including the medicare co-payment .
in the past week , abbott has faced widespread internal and external criticism of his decision last week to knight prince philip .
outgoing local government minister , david crisafulli , is one of the ministers to lose his seat .
here he is on the twitters chatting to shadow treasurer ( potentially incoming treasurer ) curtis pitt .
awwwwwww .

labor is currently on 43 seats and lnp on 39 in the counting with 71.4 % of the counting done .
45 seats are needed for a party to form government in its own right .
there are currently four seats that are in doubt - and they are really , really close .
it could be days before they are known .
in mansfield labor need a swing of 11.1 % to win and are currently on 11.2 % in maryborough alp need a swing of 0.3 % and it is currently 2.7 % .
in redlands lnp hold it on a margin of 21.1 % and there is currently a 20.2 % swing against it .
in whitsunday , lnp have a margin of 10.7 % and there is currently a swing of 10.5 % .
about 70 % of votes have been counted so the number of seats in doubt can go up and down by the hour .
bridie jabour ( @ bkjabour ) these four seats in doubt are so close .
look at those swings compared to the margins .

with a labor victory looking likely queensland could soon again have state sanctioned ceremonies for civil unions for same-sex couples .
annastacia palaszczuk committed to reinstating the ceremonies during the campaign after they were scrapped by the liberal national party in 2012 .
civil unions for same sex couples were introduced during the dying days of the anna bligh labor government and opposed by many sections of the liberal national party .
campbell newman himself is a supporter of same-sex marriage but was forced to wind back the laws by the more conservative arm of the lnp .

he refused to say what would happen to the laws during the 2012 campaign and then scrapped the ceremonies , so same-sex couples could only register their relationship with the government and have a private ceremony is they wished .

documents.title: kate jones : newman gracious in defeat
text: kate jones , who defeated campbell newman in his seat of ashgrove , has spoken this morning and said newman was very gracious in defeat when he called her last night .

on the message labor has taken from the huge seat win : annastacia was very humbled by the result last night , what we saw last night was a very clear message from queensland , they do n't want their assets sold and they want a government that listens and has a more consensual style .
we do n't even know what the numbers are but i think overwhelmingly there 's a very clear message .

documents.title: campbell newman phones annastacia palaszczuk
text: but not to concede defeat .
he says he has called her to congratulate her on the success of labor candidates in the election .
newman will remain premier until the result is known , which i did n't think was ever in doubt !
campbell newman ( @ theqldpremier ) today i phoned @ twitterid to congratulate her on her candidates ' success .
i 'll continue as caretaker until the result is known # qldpols

documents.title: tony abbott plays down federal impact on queensland result
text: the prime minister has conceded while he does have lessons to learn from the queensland election result , federal issues did not have much impact on the campaign .
tony abbott just spoke to reporters in sydney and said he really felt for campbell newman .

he 's been a good premier who led a good government , obviously there are lessons , the lessons are not to give up on reform but to make sure everything you propose is fully explained and justified , and we have to learn that in canberra as well .
asked if he took any responsibility for the queensland state election result abbott said he watched some of the people 's forum and the leaders ' debate and no federal issues were raised .
( which is incorrect , the gp co-payment was raised at the people 's forum ) .
he says while knighting prince philip was a distraction for couple of days , voters judge state elections on state issues and federal elections on federal issues .
i am determined to ensure that australia does not join the weak government club of the world .
i 'm not going to be distracted from giving australians the good government it deserves in the end government is not a popularity contest , it 's a competency contest .
clive palmer 's palmer 's united party failed to up a single seat in queensland though it did manage to score 5 % of the primary vote .

palmer 's star candidate and queensland state leader , john bjelke-petersen , the son of the infamous joh , gave the deputy premier , jeff seeney , a run for his money in callide , but ultimately failed to prevail .
with 57.9 % of the vote counted seeney looks set to retain on 56.8 % of the vote to bjelke-petersen 's 43.2 % after preferences are distributed .
seeney did suffer a swing of 6.7 % against him though .
the result leaves palmer with no mps in the queensland parliament despite an election with a huge protest vote .
premier campbell newman actually looked quite relieved in his speech last night after losing ashgrove .
he spoke frankly , and was quite emotional at times .
i recommend watching , it was one of his most authentic moments of the election .
campbell newman speaks on election night
annastacia palaszczuk said last night she was hopeful of forming government .
it is looking more likely labor will form government than the lnp with labor currently on 44 seats with 70 % of the vote counted .
to form government , 45 seats are required .
her full speech on election night is below .
annastacia palaszczuk speaks on election night
the aftershocks of the queensland election are really being felt in canberra , particularly in the prime minister 's office .
tony abbott is making all the same mistakes campbell newman did , guardian australia 's political editor , lenore taylor , writes in her analysis here .
newman seemed to think queenslanders would come around if he just said the word strong lots of times .
the abbott government seems to have the same expectations of the phrases debt and deficit disaster and cleaning up labor 's mess .
but those phrases do not substitute for clear explanations about why the federal government thinks its chosen spending cuts are the best and fairest ways to improve the budget bottom line .
michelle grattan writes that the queensland election puts in lights that the coalition federal government could be a one term government , over at the conversation .

state factors especially the government 's assets leasing plan , newman 's cuts and his arrogant style - were the primary drivers of the queensland result , as labor 's wayne swan conceded on abc tv .
but abbott is clothed in some of the blame and , given his weakened position , the implications for him will be very serious .

documents.title: tony abbott : there are lessons in queensland result
text: prime minister tony abbott says there are lessons in the queensland election outcome for the federal government in his first statement on the result , calling it difficult .
there are lessons in this result for all governments , including the federal one .
the lnp will be looking at them closely .
the federal government remains fully committed to creating jobs and helping families get ahead .
abbott says he has called newman and thanked him for his service .
obviously , it has been a very difficult outcome for him and his government .

documents.title: campbell newman : i 'm just a guy with one vote now .
text: campbell newman has been caught by media getting into his car this morning .
he offered only one comment : i 'm just a guy with one vote now .

the courier mail 's queensland state political editor , steve wardill , says last night 's result does not mean the end of reform governments , it is a reflection on campbell newman 's leadership style and his pugnacious approach .
you can read it here .
over three years , newman deflated the lnp 's support base more than he inflated it .

the most sobering fact for them all is that one of queensland 's smallest-ever oppositions , with its largely unknown leader and no real policy platform , just knocked off a powerful premier with an unprecedented majority .
the wash-up can not ignore that newman 's approach to the foreign environment he found himself from 2012 was the catalyst for this predicament .
newman lacked the emotional investment in what it took the lnp to gain government compared to those who did the hard years in opposition .
he measured this investment only by the risk he undertook to get there and , at times , approached the job more concerned with his own legacy in mind rather than longevity .
campbell newman is not the only senior lnp member to lose his seat with some ministers and assistant ministers staring down the barrel of defeat in their electorates .
the police minister , jack dempsey , and local government minister , david crisafulli , have suffered double digit swings in their electorates and are certain to lose their seat .
in dempsey 's seat of bundaberg there 's been a swing of 23.8 % against with dempsey sitting on 44 % of the primary vote after preferences .
64.2 % of the votes have been counted .
in crisafulli 's seat of mundingburra there is a swing of 13 % against him and labor is sitting on 52.9 % of the primary vote after preferences .
75 % of the vote has been handed .
assistant ministers robert cavallucci , saxon rice and gavin king , are also likely to lose their seats .
rice unseated the labor treasurer andrew fraser at the 2012 election in the brisbane seat of mt coot-tha but there has now been an 8.2 % swing against her .
opposition leader , bill shorten , is on insiders this morning saying federal issues were part of the result in the queensland election last night .
there are state issues , privatisation , regional queensland is calling out for attention from the lnp but there were federal issues at stake .
tony abbott would n't go to queensland for one month but his presence was felt .
shorten said campbell newman 's leadership style was a significant factor but he keeps going back to abbott .

nothing can take away from what annastacia palaszczuk and queensland labor accomplished , but it 's the issues that matter to voters education , healthcare , jobs and keeping promises and all of those [ state and federal ] issues blurred .
it 's the way both levels of liberal government have conducted themselves [ that has turned voters off ] .
a penny for a media mogul 's thoughts : rupert murdoch ( @ rupertmurdoch ) shock turnover in q'land outing okay govt blank cheque to nobodies .
ca n't ignore this a huge message to feds .
people have spoken !
queensland wakes without an election result being declared after neither party won enough seats last night to form government in its own right .

labor still may get over the line with abc calling 44 seats declared in its hands , up from just nine seats , and the liberal national party on 33 seats , reduced from 73 , with 70 % of the vote counted .
last night the lnp seats stood at 40 .
katter 's australian party has two seats and independent peter wellington has one so they could potentially become the balance of power in a minority parliament .
the result has ramifications in canberra with the pressure on tony abbott 's prime ministership increasing after the result .
federal mp jane prentice refused to endorse him as prime minister last night .
the liberal national party is searching for a new leader after premier campbell newman lost the seat of ashgrove to kate jones .
the party could meeting today to elect a new leader .
as we wait for government to be formed you can read through election night as it happened here .
